crops.origin: France; grown in the Pyrenees; originally from Liberia
crops.institution_involved: Station de Pathologie Vegetale, Pont de la Maye, Gironde
crops.description: A hardy perennial, grown in the Pyrenees, but originally from Liberia.

crops.institution_involved: Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum, Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.description: An erect shrub or small tree with obtusely lobed leathery leaves, broader than long, and few-flowered clusters of pure yellow flowers. Native to India. For previous introduction see 98802.

crops.origin: Union of South Africa; native to southern Africa
crops.institution_involved: McGregor Museum, Kimberley
crops.description: A strongly resin-scented shrub with oblong to obovate, entire leaves up to 2 inches long and short racemes of small woolly flower heads; said to be a good stock feed and drought resistant. For previous introduction see 98012.

crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A South African bulbous plant with six to nine linear-subulate, channeled, hairy leaves about a foot long and green, yellow-margined flowers in a lax raceme on a scape as long as the leaves.

crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A handsome tropical tree with ovate-oblong acute leaves and very numerous pale-rose flowers in much-branched terminal panicles; larger in all parts than Lagerstroemia indica.

crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A tall tropical tree 70 to 100 feet high, with elliptic-lanceolate leaves 3 to 6 inches long, hairy beneath, and purple flowers in axillary and terminal panicles; much larger than Lagerstroemia indica, but with less showy flowers.

crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A tropical banana relative about 12 feet high, with leaves 7 feet long and fruits about 4 inches long. For previous introduction see 75282.

crops.origin: India; native to India and tropical America
crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A bulbous perennial 12 to 18 inches high; the flower scape, appearing before the linear leaves, bears a raceme 6 to 12 inches long of drooping campanulate flowers about an inch long, greenish white with green nerves. For previous introduction see 103630.

crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A bulbous plant, unknown except in cultivation, with linear bright-green leaves about a foot long and bright-yellow, red, or white flowers over an inch long on scapes about 5 inches high. For previous introduction see 68125.

crops.institution_involved: Chacra Experimental de Alto de Sierra, San Juan
crops.description: Common wheat seed lot designated Alto de Sierra, 01-4, from Argentina.

crops.description: Common wheat seed lot designated Alto de Sierra, 01-10-d4, from Argentina.

crops.origin: Nanking, China; collected in Kwangsi Province at Ta Tseh Tsuen, Yung Hsien, at 1,000 feet altitude
crops.presented_by: A. N. Steward and H. C. Cheo
crops.institution_involved: University of Nanking
crops.description: Collected October 23, 1933, at Ta Tseh Tsuen, Yung Hsien, at 1,000 feet altitude. A tree with ovate fruits an inch long and almost as wide. Numbered in September 1934.
